  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\nissue is only for iOS <-> Android; iOS <-> iOS; \r\nWorks fine on Android <-> Android\r\nContact \"Watson\" adds contact \"Hudson\" to his Contacts. For added Hudson:\r\n1. there is no empty chat shown in Chats untill Watson will not send a message\r\n2. As soon as 1st message is sent by Watson then Hudson can see new chat with that message\r\n3. In a new 1-1 chat for Hudson there is no \"Add to Contacts\" button, so she can't add this contact to the Contacts\r\n4. No commands except @browse are shown to Hudson in 1-1 chat (even after relaunch)\r\n5. Send message received by Hudson is shown as plain text\r\n6. Request message received by Hudson is shown as empty box\r\n\r\n\r\nExpected: \r\n2. Empty 1-1 chat is shown to Hudson after Watson added her to his contacts\r\n3. 1-1 chat for Hudson contains \"Add to Contacts\" button\r\n4. commands like \"send\", \"request\", \"location\" are shown in 1-1 chat for Hudson\r\n\r\n\r\n![img_0514](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/28712304-097815b8-738b-11e7-884c-809a68764fdf.jpg)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- as Watson: scan QR code for Hudson and add her to the contacts\r\n- as Hudson: check Chats for new 1-1 chat with new contact. Wait for 1-2 minutes\r\n- as Watson: send her new text message\r\n- as Hudson: check new 1-1 chat with a contact and find \"Add to Contacts\" button and other commands, e.g. \"send\" - not shown currently\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: develop 0.9.9d103\r\n* Operating System: \r\nReal device Samsung Galaxy S6, Android 6.0.1\r\nReal device iPhone 6s, iOS 10.2.1",
